Class EldManager

      • RequestDebugData

        public EldBleError RequestDebugData()
        Request debug data from the ELD device and uploaded to the IOSiX servers for troubleshooting vehicle connectivity issues.

        Calling app should ensure internet connectivity is available and the device is connected to the phone prior to request debug information. Visit http://fleet.iosix.com/eld/debug.php?action=last&mac=XXXXXXXXXXXX in a web browser (substituting in the MAC address of the relevant device) to check if we have received the most recent debug report for a device

        Returns:
        Status of request

      • RequestRecord

        public EldBleError RequestRecord()
        Request the oldest record stored on the ELD. Actual data is returned in the callback (EldBleDataCallback). 

         NOTE:
 To achieve maximum throughput when requesting many records from the ELD we recommend the following procedure:
      1. request 10 records, for example from 1 to 10
      2. Wait until all records are received
      3. call deleteRecord method with parameters 1, 10
      4. Repeat

        Returns:
        Status of the request

      • RequestRecord

        public EldBleError RequestRecord(int recNo)
        Request a cached record from the ELD by sequence number.
        Actual data is returned in the callback (EldBleDataCallback). Check EldBufferRecord for valid range. 

         NOTE:
 To achieve maximum throughput when requesting many records from the ELD we recommend the following procedure:
      1. request 10 records, for example from 1 to 10
      2. Wait until all records are received
      3. call deleteRecord method with parameters 1, 10
      4. Repeat

        Parameters:
        recNo - Sequence number of cached record to request
        Returns:
        Status of the request

      • ResetBleWatchdog

        public EldBleError ResetBleWatchdog()
        Reset the Bluetooth watchdog timer on the connected ELD.

        ELD supports an optional 25 second Bluetooth watchdog for active confirmation of the connection status. If you wish to use this feature, this function must be called to reset that timer, otherwise the ELD will initiate a bluetooth disconnection. If you do not call this function, the Bluetooth watchdog will not start and never needs to be reset.

        Returns:
        EldBleError
        Since:
        Firmware v304
